Package: rixpress
Title: Build Reproducible Analytical Pipelines With Nix
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Bruno", "Rodrigues", , "bruno@brodrigues.co", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Streamlines the creation of reproducible analytical pipelines
    using `default.nix` expressions generated via `{rix}` for reproducibility.
	Define derivations in R or Python, chain them into a dependency-driven DAG,
	assemble complete workflows and build the pipeline using
	Nix as the underlying end-to-end build tool. Heavily inspired by the `{targets}` package.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
URL: https://github.com/b-rodrigues/rixpress/, https://b-rodrigues.github.io/rixpress/
BugReports: https://github.com/b-rodrigues/rixpress/issues
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    igraph,
    jsonlite,
    processx
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Suggests:
    dplyr,
    knitr,
    reticulate,
